eous regions while preserving sharp edges. The entire framework is trained end-to-end using only bounding box labels, with losses including detection accuracy, mask-box IoU consistency, topology regularization, and certainty-preserving smoothness. TPSR-Net is especially effective for small, irregular damages where traditional WSSS methods fail due to sparse activation. We validate on CTDet and introduce a new benchmark, DamageCity, synthesized from urban infrastructure images with diverse damage types and occlusion levels. Our method achieves state-of-the-art performance in pixel-level localization without requiring mask annotations, offering a practical solution for automated structural health monitoring.",
